INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(391, 1314, '2007-09-11 10:42:59', 're:Officer Forum', 390, 55, '2007-09-11 10:42:59', 'My more important issue is gearing up and skilling people.\r\n\r\nI do not think we are ready for kara as a guild. I think we need more dps for one which comes with better gear. I think we should also work on gearing up our tanks for kara. Some fight may need resist gear if this is the case we should work on getting that made for the mT and OT. The healers were having a hard time keeping people up in kara again this comes easier with better gear,more mana +healing ect. \r\n\r\nI think we have some players that are not very great at their classes. This is something we need to work on by bring them into instances 1 at a time and helping them learn. For instance I went into SV with calta and he could not keep up with heals. Maybe he needs to speak with his CL on how he can improve that.  Everyone should know the basics of their class mages should be quick with sheep/resheep,hunters should know how to keep things traped,rogues should know how to sap and dps,healers should be able to heal ect. I know sometimes things go wrong and these things just don\\''t work but everyone should have the basics down, and in my honest opinion we have some players that don\\''t.\r\n\r\nWorking on helping people level is a good thing we don\\''t want anyone to feel left out but we need to be on track with our goals. If our goal is kara then we should be working on getting in there geared and prepared to rock the place down. Maybe should have 2 nights a week for helping the 60-69 players and spend the rest of the week working on getting the 70\\''s what they need to be able to go to kara and make us sucessful. Again it\\''s all about what our main goal is as a guild and for us to move further we need to do it together as a team. We need to learn to work well with each other and switching people around when we instance would make this easier. Ok those are y thoughts atm.\r\n\r\n', 'no', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(392, 1312, '2007-09-11 12:55:18', 're:Officer Forum', 390, 55, '2007-09-11 12:55:18', 'Thank you Tiger,\r\n\r\nI agree with everything you\\''re saying.\r\n\r\nI think a major issue of ours at the moment is not WHAT we need to be doing, we all seem to be in agreement, but rather HOW we are going to accomplish these things. At least that is what I am sensing here.\r\n\r\nJust so that we are clear on our goals as a guild, I am going to make a new \\"Rule\\" on the rules page. We can put what our current goal is, and modify it as our goals change.\r\n\r\nHere\\''s something to think about:\r\n\r\nWhen I went to kara for the first time, our group did not have any \\"heroic\\" gear on. Most players had about 80% (lvl 70) blues and couple of greens. We were able to kill 4 bosses. We even one shotted Moroes. We could have kept going after the Opera event, but it was really late. I do not think our gear had anything to do with our success that night.\r\n\r\nI believe everyone has potential to be great players. \r\nGear is one thing, Skill is another. I\\''d prefer someone with greater skill any day than someone decked out in AH epics.\r\n\r\nI am only mentioning this, because one of my pet peeves is that people blame their gear for not being able to compensate for skill. I personally view this line of thinking as negative, and I have seen it first hand. \r\n\r\nDon\\''t get me wrong, we\\''re not going into Kara with level 35 greens. That won\\''t happen. We do need to get better gear, because there is always an upgrade. But it is my personal belief that we can skip heroic instance gear, I\\''ve seen it done.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'no', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(393, 1314, '2007-09-11 13:59:32', '(Heroics)', 393, 55, '2007-09-11 13:59:32', 'Yes I agree we do not need heroic instance gear to do kara, however we do need to be wearing blue that are made for our level. I do not know what everyone is wearing for gear but I can speak for myself to say I still am wearing lvl 66 gear. Heroics are hard,sometimes harder than a kara boss so I do not think we need heroic gear just some nice upgrades. \r\n\r\nAs far as HOW we accomplish what needs to be done I am not sure. Lets throw a couple ideas around with some of the issues at hand. As far as getting people skilled that takes time and work. If we work with someone we notice has a hard time bring them through some places and point out some things that may help. \r\n\r\nI know it\\''s discouraging to go on a guild run and wipe time after time on one part of an instance. It may turn some people off from the guild so I would suggest we take the underskilled players we notice in one at a time so there is not a bunch of chaos.', 'yes', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(394, 1314, '2007-09-11 14:12:23', 're:Officer Forum', 390, 55, '2007-09-11 14:12:23', 'I agree we do not heroic gear to do kara. Heroics are hard sometimes harder than kara bosses from what I hear. I do not know what everyones gear looks like but I think we need atleast blues of our level. Speaking for myself I am still wearing lvl 66 gear in some slots  not sure about the rest of the guild. We do need to work on skill because with no skill will go nowhere. So we need to adress the players we see lacking in skill and take them places and help them out.', 'no', '', 0);
