INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(409, 1335, '2007-09-13 07:46:19', 'Hammer and his key.', 409, 55, '2007-09-13 07:46:19', 'Hammerlord got his key last night. I don\\''t know if it was with a guild group or not.  It was after I logged when he got it though. But if he pugged it, I\\''m kinda worried. We\\''re obviously doing something wrong if we can\\''t clear BM without a wipe or two. I don\\''t know if its a class issue or what. But the whole idea bears some thought if we\\''re gonna try for farming Kara.\r\nInputs appreciated.', 'yes', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(410, 1312, '2007-09-13 13:58:02', 're:Hammer and his key.', 409, 55, '2007-09-13 13:58:02', 'I think we\\''re doing just fine. I am pleased that he got his key.\r\n\r\nInputs:\r\n#1 It was hammers first time in BM with us so he was learning it while we were doing it. Which goes to show that he picks up quite fast. #2 There were multiple issues where we made stupid mistakes that happen now and then, not anything to be worried about. \r\n\r\nThe biggest thing I can see is that we weren\\''t getting the adds cleared fast enough. The elites were going down, but the adds were still up each time a new portal spawned. The adds have to go down faster. I recommended that tiger places explosive traps and erry get closer to tiger to get the adds down. This could have made the difference. I didn\\''t hear anyone else making any comments about how to get them down quicker, I was only offering suggestions.\r\n\r\nI see the BM runs as successful last nite because #1 Several upgrades were taken and #2 We learned more about the encounter #3 we got lots of rep for what its worth... All in all, a win win situation\r\n\r\nAs far as us farming kara we are not going to farm it tomorrow nite. Get used to that fact. It may take a long time. If you continue to doubt our abilities then you\\''re part of the problem, not part of the solution. As if you couldn\\''t tell by now, negativity is one of my biggest pet peeves, it counts for nothing.\r\n\r\nWe should press on and continue to learn as much as we can, it only makes us stronger. If someone pugs something for a key or gear, then so be it.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'no', '', 0);
