INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(431, 1314, '2007-09-27 11:36:01', 'Guild issues', 431, 55, '2007-09-27 11:36:01', 'I have a few issues that need to be adressed this post may be a little long please be patient.\r\n\r\nIssue 1) The direction of the guild\r\n\r\nAs an Officer I have no idea what the diection of the guild is. With that said a member must be confused as to what direction the guild is going and what they can get out of it.  Are we a rading guild or a casual guild? A place to go and have fun or a place to learn and experience new things? This is something we need to decide on and stick with it. Our goals rules and overall guild atmosphere must go with what kind of guild we are and where we want to go. \r\n\r\nIssue 2) Members not knowing their classes\r\nWe have a lot of members that do not have a clue how to play their class or spec correctly. This is something that will hold us back when we try to accomplish things and be successful. We need to have a CL for each class and make sure they are doing their job teaching players how to grp,raid and learn what spec works best for them. This is something that is very important and needs to be done. I don\\''t mind offering tips to members but if it\\''s a class I don\\''t play often I shouldn\\''t be the one they are talking to, as a CL would have much better info and knowledge on the subject. \r\n\r\nIssue 3) Losing members\r\nWe are going to lose people no matter how hard we try to make everyone happy. Unfortunately that is just the way it is in a guild people come people go. However I am noticing a trend of people leveling up and getting frags thenleaving for another guild. It seems as though we are a stepping guild, a place to come and get help leveling up and even help getting keyed before they move onto a more active guild. I see this happening more often in the future if we do not come together and decide where this guild is going.\r\n\r\nIssue 4) Getting too far ahead of our goals\r\nBeing positive is a great thing honestly,I wish everyone had a positive outlook on things. But being too positive will cause a down fall in the guild. Our goal on the site is kara and taking down boss #1. That is a great goal and if we want to be more positive and up the guild spirit we should be looking to down boss #2 or 3. I think Gruul\\''s is too far ahead of our goals and having a sign up or even talking about raiding it will become a down fall as our goal is boss #1 in kara and that hasn\\''t even been completed yet. We need to take small steps and accomplish them before thinking of taking leaps. If we focus on the small steps one at a time mebers will be proud when they accomplish them and be ready to take the next one with a positive attitude. We will wipe and we will learn but we will all be on the same step and not looking too far ahead dicouraing people from accomplishing what they set out to do.\r\n\r\nIssue 5) Guild involvement\r\nOk we run people for frags and do BM and get them keyed....That is great really. The problem is that not every member wants to be running frags and BM all the time they want to run things besides that. I know there have been issues on running heroics but the more expireinced people are going to want to run them and see what they are about and get some nice loot. Heroics are also a good way to learn how to perfect your class as they are difficult and you need to depend on each class doing their job to succeed. Other than heroics we should be running things for people to get them rep gear and just experience grping. For this SV SH SL even durnholde are great choices as they are challenging but easy if played correctly. We must give people an option rather than have them get bored and move on to a more active guild.\r\n\r\nIssue 6)Raiding\r\nI read the new raid rules and I was very happy about them however I think we want to be sucessful we need to take it further. I have been a few different raiding guilds and the atmosphere while raiding was always the same. There was one raid leader firmly giving instrustions the entire time on vent and an assistant typing out whatever needed to be typed out. Class leads had a channel to talk to their classes if their was any confusion or misunderstandings. There shouldn\\''t be 10 people talking on vent or even 5 for that matter, only the raid leader the MT and the asstant should be speaking unless it\\''s something \\"I\\''m down\\" \\"pick up roange\\" ect. While the pulls and boss fights are going on there should be no nonsense talking going on. Again we need CLs to make sure that people know what to do and how to do it correctly. Each person has a job and for us to succeed they need to be doing their job to their best ability. If someone does something wrong let them know don\\''t be afraid to hurt feelings, they need to be taught how to do their job. I\\''m not saying be a rude ass to them but let them know what they did wrong.\r\n\r\nIssue 7) Officer discussions\r\n\r\nThere have been a few times that we didn\\''t agree on an issue and that is fine, we are not always going to agree. However we need to learn to open the issue up and solve it with rational discussion rather than fighting or pointing fingers. Everyone has a right to their own opinion and we should be hearing each other out not critisizing each other for what we think. Lately when their has been an issue it has not been solved but rather  we argue then say w/e just drop it....that is not a good thing because the issue is still there and still needs to be worked out. We are officers and we help run a guild the members depend and trust our judgement we should have the faith they have in us in each other. If we can not all agree on a certain issue then we should vote on that issue after we have all discussed it and stated our opinions. We can\\''t leave matters unsettled because we are afraid to have a discussion, that is our job we need to do it and not be afraid to hold back.\r\n\r\nThese are some of the issues I see that need to be adressed quickly for this guild to move forward and be sucessful. I think we should hold an officer meeting to discuss them also.', 'yes', '', 0);
