INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(433, 1321, '2007-09-28 03:02:31', 're:Guild issues', 431, 55, '2007-09-28 03:02:31', 'Nice post, definately touches base with a lot of issues going on ATM. lookin at the past week  it also seems like we may need to open recruitment b/c its the same 10 ppl on every day (ie), there is no guild participation minus . Ok so who need help? oh me me i need the xx frag. Nothing is being said in guild chat at all we need to find a way to open ppl up and socialize. Out of all the servers n guilds ive played in this is definately the quiest which is going to turn people off (serious players) b/c they want to stay active, the more casual i log once a month type players ya they will stay b/c they are being pushed to succeed. Just a little more of a view that i forsee if you will. ', 'no', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(434, 1312, '2007-09-28 15:03:27', 're:Guild issues', 431, 55, '2007-09-28 15:03:27', 'I just want to say that I agree with some of that but some of it I don''t.\r\n\r\n1) We are a guild. What kind of guild? Have we raided kara? Yes. By definition it makes us a raiding guild. It shouldn''t matter what label we put here, this is a guild, and either you are part of it, or you just accepted the guild invite. We have rules and a raid schedule. I am not sure I agree with what was said on this, if there is a way to solve this problem, then please explain. If it is simple as calling us a Raiding Guild, then ok we are a Raiding Guild - Problem solved.\r\n\r\n2) The last time I looked we had 4 class leaders. Since that time 1 has left the guild. If we want to fill the CL roles, then lets hear some ideas as to who would be good for it. Until that time we either have to 1) Deal with it or 2) Help them in our capacity.\r\n\r\n3) Yes people will leave, I have no problems with that.  As far as people using us as  a stepping stone to get keyed and what not, i don''t want to see us doing anything different. If people choose to leave it is their business, until that time they should be afforded every opportunity as an ONO member.\r\n \r\n4) If we aren''t planning for the future then we are going to stagnate, and then people WILL leave this guild. I think we should be looking at Gruul and even beyond that. It is true that we haven''t got Kara going yet, but Gruul is a whole seperate encounter. I will continue to schedule the Gruul''s raids using the same methodology as the kara raids. If we get enough people signed up we will go. If you personally don''t want to go, so be it.\r\n\r\n5) Lets get perfectly clear on this issue of heroics / dungeons, and getting keyed for kara. I don''t mind if people are running heroics. I just don''t want to see a divide where half the guild is always doing heroics and not helping with the other half. For instance, if I see someone asking for part of their kara key, and no one says anything but then someone gets a heroic dungeon going after that... It is a problem. As far as getting gear or what not from dungeons, I believe that heroics can be skipped entirely.\r\n\r\n6) The raid rules can be updated by any one of us reading this. If you want to update them, please feel free, just make a post in here explaining what you did, and if we don''t like it we''ll let you know.\r\n\r\n7) Officer stuff... Lets get on with it we have a guild to run. If you''re constantly gonna go against what is said then maybe the issue lies somewhere besides where you think. You all should know by now that I am one of the least greedy people around and I have some values that I think should be infused into this guild. Stuff like integrity and doing what is right. Sometimes this may come out if I see something happening that doesn''t agree with what I believe should be happening. I''ll probably do it again in the future, but if it does happen I can guarantee each of you that it will be for the guild, and not for myself. This is something that you all must think about. Why would I argue with someone, especially if I am friends with the person. It comes down to this... I created this guild because I felt like I had what it takes. I invited each of you here, and I also asked you to be officers because I felt like I could trust in you and help me to lead the guild where I want it. If this doesn''t sound like what you signed up for then maybe it is time you should be asking yourself why you''re an officer here.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'no', '', 0);
