INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(442, 1335, '2007-10-17 19:30:16', 'Weighted Dice.', 442, 55, '2007-10-06 22:26:34', 'Yes, this thread is about DKP.  I get the feeling DKP might help us with the motivation problem we have with member signing up. So taken from my old guild here is what I am going to propose. This isn\\''t in any way set in stone, but it worked very well for my last guild.\r\n\r\nWeighted Dice:\r\n\r\nYour DKP alters your dice roll.  If you have 0 dkp you roll 1-100. If you have 30 dkp you roll 30 -100.\r\n\r\nDKP is earned through a few ways.\r\n\r\n+1 dkp for being at the raid at the form up time without a summon.\r\n+4 dkp for being ready at the start of the raid. (as in your ready to smack the first pice of trash at the minute of the raid start time)\r\n+5 dkp for staying until the raid is called to a stop. ( i.e. the raid is over)\r\n+10 dkp for boss killed. (modified by guild progression)\r\n+15 dkp for full clear of the instance.\r\n\r\nYour total DKP affects your weighted dice roll. You have 400 dkp, you roll 400 -400. This will help to prevent people from hording dkp so folks in the raid will benefit from that person using his dkp to gain gear. (So spending 400 dkp on a junk wand will really make the person think twice.) On the same note if someone gains enough dkp and no items of note drops, that person wastes a lot of time and effort on an item that isn\\''t worth what they put into it. Its the only real flaw in this system that I have seen. But I have seen it work. The question will be how will we work something like for alts that we have to bring? Does one account have one DKP list that they can use on all of their toons or should each toon have a seperate dkp list?\r\nFor the record I know this system works, and its fair compared to the other systems i\\''ve seen except for the instance of people not having anything to roll on.\r\nComment are appreciated. And no I didn\\''t use my old hardcore guild\\''s loot system. Yall woulda prolly lynched me. :P\r\n\r\n', 'yes', '', 25);
