INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(449, 1312, '2007-10-10 07:58:43', 're:Weighted Dice.', 442, 55, '2007-10-10 07:58:43', 'Ok thank you Terik for posting about DKP, and also I haven\\''t been able to really get on here and look at it as I have had unexpected company for the last week.\r\n\r\nYes, I say we implement this as it would help out progression toward our real goals. \r\n\r\nWe can do DKP based on the PERSON rather than the TOON. I am all for that because I know that on more than one occasion I have had to swap out mid-raid and it wouldn\\''t be fair to me or anyone else who did that.\r\n\r\nI would assume that the DKP will be carried over if the person does not roll on something. ie; you have 40 DKP before the raid, then you do the raid and earn another 40 DKP. At the end, you add the two together and have 80 DKP for the next raid.\r\n\r\nWhat I am confused about is where you said if you roll on something it will be all or nothing? ie; I have 80 DKP, and I want to use my DKP to roll on a super bow of massacre blood letting. That means I will be rolling 80-100? Does my DKP expire at that point if I lose my roll?\r\n\r\nAnyhow, I say we implement it right away\r\n', 'no', '', 0);
