INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(454, 1321, '2007-10-11 22:14:41', 'Cleanining House', 454, 55, '2007-10-11 22:14:41', 'Couple things on my Agenda: \r\n\r\n1. This guild needs major improvement on the guildies ( yes its been stated in g chat officers cnt babysit them but its time to enforce it) We just overall have to stop bending over backwards for ppl b/c they \\"know we will do it\\" people that come with and help we return the favor obviously.\r\n\r\n2. A lot of guildies are gettin bummed that they sign up for 5 mans and cant even get those going, mandingo for one is dying to get with us in Kara (also a healer) and Bm didnt happen again tonite b/c not enough people on. Including people that signed up. Again dkp issue/if your not gna have enough courtesy to show up for something you signed up for then please dont do it and leave the slots open that way we can always say you know what not enough people were signed up, we asked people online at the time and noone was interested. Not personal attks on anyone but you have to look at it from outside of the box and ask yourself how does this look to others. \r\n\r\n3. I got a tad bit of information about raiding with Unleashed and possibliity of it being tomorrow night Oct 12. Not sure if that is valid or if it was misinterpreted (sp?) for a follwoing week but we do have 9 signed up granted we need one less dps for one more tank n healer. My question is are we sacrificing our guild run (4 others) to let Unleashed in? If that is the case i think that will cause turmoil since we stated 1st come 1st serve. \r\n\r\nOnly solution i can propose to this is tell people str8 out we are startin an evaluation period for the entire guild including the officers/gm/ point being EVERYONE. We are going to be calculating participation and be judging whether or not you are right for this guild if they have problems with the issue that they can address one of us personally by whisper or type the cmd we all know /gquit now b/c we are lookin to form a solid helpful guild not a selfish well im pvp\\''n or im doin this sorry i cant hlp this person or that. \r\n\r\nagain this is no way shape or form attacks on anyone im just tired of seeing this guild dive bomb and we need to salvage it before we hit the pavement.', 'yes', '', 5);
INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(455, 1312, '2007-10-11 23:27:57', 're:Cleanining House', 454, 55, '2007-10-11 23:27:57', '> Only solution i can propose to this is tell people str8 out we are startin an evaluation period for the entire guild including the officers/gm/\r\n\r\nCareful what you say there lost, we don\\''t need to be evaluated this is our guild.\r\nI couldn\\''t make it tonight because of personal issues if you want to -DKP me for it go ahead but I am starting to sense that you and maybe others don\\''t really like it that I am GM and that I state my mind on occasion, and this is some of it coming out. We know where we stand as far as helping people out, but let me make this clear, just because other people aren\\''t stepping us is no reason to stop helping people yourself. Saying this we all need to take a look at where we stand on that because letting the guild stagnate because we don\\''t want to do anything to help because we\\''re \\"burned out\\"  is not the answer.\r\n\r\nIf you don\\''t want to be officer anymore that\\''s fine, but don\\''t make any attacks aimed at me, or other officers because you\\''re unsatisfied with how things are going. I think I am a pretty good GM, and I know that some of you will argue that because I may have stated my mind once or twice about how I think officers should be behaving. I have worked my ass off trying to get us raiding, and if you can\\''t see it then you need to open your eyes. \r\n\r\nFor some reason, a lot of players in our guild are not coming online recently. The only reason I can think of that this is happening is that they have other interests going on. One thing that I can think of that I have heard at least twice is that people have Halo3 or some other form of entertainment. There\\''s absolutely nothing we can do about it.\r\n\r\nAs far as PvP people, yes they need to get out of the battlegrounds and help out. The people who ask for stuff once or twice in guild chat shouldn\\''t be brushed off. If you want to start telling people they need to help out or /gquit then I think that would cause a problem.\r\n\r\nUnleashed is in Alliance with us now and we will be raiding with them, please put any differences aside and lets get on with raiding. I think that once people see us getting into kara more often with our alliance it will get them thinking and it will determine if they want to go or not and will give us the boost to become self sufficient in the long run.\r\n\r\nFor those that still want to PvP or screw off in other ways then they will be passed over.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'no', '', 0);
