INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(457, 1314, '2007-10-12 08:48:09', 're:Cleanining House', 454, 55, '2007-10-12 08:48:09', 'I agree with lost on the fact that the officers are doing far too much helping while the other members don\\''t really offer much help. I myself and getting a little burt out with running the same thing 40 times. If people want to raid they should be helping their guild mates get keyed it shouldn\\''t rely on the officers shoulders. I think the DKP system may motivate people to get in gear and show up for raids,key newer 70\\''s ect. \r\n\r\nThe fact that we can not get a 5 man going is sad yes but I don\\''t see what we can do about it really. If people chose to go that\\''s great but if they are doing their own thing and want to keep doing it we can\\''t really say much to that. \r\n\r\nI don\\''t have a problem with you being GM Dardel and as far as not showing up for some things,I understand that you have RL to deal with and a new baby to take care of. I have been there as a GM and conflicting betewwen the guild and my RL almost ruined my RL. So in that aspect I can understand where your coming from. I think you try hard to get things going in the guild and the officer are also trying hard as well. \r\n\r\nI think getting into kara more often and being sucessful at taking down bosses is what is going to make most of our members happy. And with a merger or alliance wit Unleashed I\\''m hoping this tuns a new page for us and we can do our weekly kara runs with 0 cancels.', 'no', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(458, 1335, '2007-10-12 13:04:19', 're:Weighted Dice.', 442, 55, '2007-10-12 13:04:19', 'Well here is the final draft for DKP and guild loot.\r\n\r\nWe will use a weighted dice system. Your DKP will affect how you roll for loot in a raid. If you have zero DKP you will roll /rand 1 100.\r\nIf you have 20 DKP, you will /rand 20 to 120. If by the next raid you have acquired 120 dkp, you will /rand 120 120. Rolling for loot with your DKP and losing the roll WILL NOT forfeit your DKP. Your DKP will continue to stack until you use it. Once you win a roll, your DKP is reset to zero. In the event of a tie; the members will /rand 1 100. The people who do not win the tie will not lose their DKP.\r\nDKP is earned for one account unless you post otherwise. If you have three alts to raid with, all three of those alts have the same DKP pool to random with. If you have someone who plays your account also, that will be up to you how you want your DKP dealt with. If you want seperate DKP pools for each toon, that must be posted prior to the first raid that this system is introduced. If you do not post that character''s name and the points are spent that is your problem. A one week grace period will be given to all existing members and to any new members that join.\r\nDKP questions or conflicts will be brought before all of the officers for consideration. Nobody will have the final authority to make decisions regarding a problem or question of DKP.\r\n\r\nRaid conduct:\r\n\r\n- You will be ready for a summon at the form up time.\r\n- You will carry the reagents to buff all of the groups you are assigned to buff with the expectation of having to buff for five wipes.\r\n- Once the start time has commenced, do not expect a break every 15 minutes. Be sure to have eaten, gathered your drinks, used the restroom, etc before we start.\r\n- Ventrillo and any other voice over internet protocol program will only be used by the officers, main tanks, class leaders, and designated individuals (healing coordinator, dps coordinator, etc). Nobody will be speaking on vent unless it is a dire emergency that will reflect the raids chances of success. If you have something to say, whisper the raid leader or the appropriate person.\r\n- If you go afk, put your /afk tag up for people to see. Inform the raid leader of approximate time length that you will be gone.\r\n\r\nFactors that will add and/or deduct DKP:\r\n(Note: it is Raid Leaders discretion to award or penalize anyone.)\r\n\r\n- If you are at the location of the raid without requiring a summon at the form up time you recieve 1 DKP.\r\n- At the start time of the raid you are ready to pull the very first mob you will earn 4 DKP. Should you be found to be afk after the ready has been initiated you will not recieve the DKP.\r\n- Staying until the raid is finished or called will earn you 5 DKP.\r\n- People on standby will be awarded the same points for being on time and ready regardless if they are drafted or not. If they park the standby character and can instantly join the raid they will acquire the points as if they had participated. If they are not used they will still acquire the points for being on time and for raid completion. This does not include boss kills and full dungeon clears. If a standby person is drafted mid-raid, they will recieve full DKP as if they had been in the raid from the start.\r\n- Bringing potions, flasks, repair bots, oils, and other items that enhance the raids chance of success will earn a set amount of DKP that is determined prior to the raid. It is not expected for anyone to provided these items; it is strictly volunteer only. You will not be reimbursed by the members. You can petition the guild master for reimbursement from the guild bank through either an item or money. The items you provide and what reward will be compensated at his discretion.\r\n- Respeccing your character for an encounter will be rewarded by a fixed value that is stated prior to the raid. The monetary compensation for the respec is between you, the raid leader, and guildmaster. Respeccing for an encounter is not mandatory, it is strictly a voluntary decision.\r\n- Slaying a boss will give you 10 DKP (depending on guild progession). The value for each boss will be set prior to every raid. For example when Attumen is on farm status he will be assigned a lower value for DKP and the next boss or encounter will have a larger value added.\r\n- Certain quests that are performed within the guild will have a value attached to them if you volunteer to help others complete the quest. An example will be running Black Morass to help key a member. That will earn you 5 points. Volunteering in itself (while commendable) is not going to be rewarded. Completing the instance or staying for three tries will be rewarded only.\r\n- Clearing a raid instance will earn 15 DKP.\r\n- Repeatedly breaking crowd control after one warning will deduct 5 DKP. Subsequent violations will bar you from the raid and possible removal from the guild.\r\n- Signing up to raid and you are not keyed or you are late without attaching a note to the raid stating your intentions will result in 5 DKP reduction.\r\n- Entering a raid instance and not having the reagents to cast group buffs for 5 wipes (note: This mean wipes not groups. If you have to buff three groups, have enough reagents to buff those three groups five times) you will be deducted 1 DKP. If the raid has wiped more often than what you have reagents for; there will be no penalty for you to hearth and purchase reagents. On certain occasions deemed as needed by the Raid Leader; you will earn 1 DKP for going to purchase reagents for yourself and other raid members. Monetary compensation is between you and the people you are buying for.\r\n- If there is a disciplinary problem (i.e. drama, using foul language, ninja looting, demotions, violation of the guild rules, etc) you will forfeit all of your DKP and be subject to being seperated from the guild.\r\n- Excessive AFK''s or absence during a raid will forfeit the DKP you would earn for that specific raid.\r\n\r\n\r\nQuests/Instances that guild members can earn DKP:\r\n\r\n- Karazhan key quest. Arcatraz, Steamvaults, Old Hillsbrad, Black Morass, and Shadowlabs will earn 5 DKP for each guild member who is in attendance.\r\n\r\nIt should be noted that an officer must be made aware at the time that instance starts to earn DKP. If there are no officers online please start a post in the general forums stating the members who were involved, who completed what quest, how many attempts, and with the date and server time it was completed. Failure to do so will not garner DKP for anyone.\r\n\r\nI highly recommend that everyone add their comments before this becomes set in stone.', 'no', '', 0);
