INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(482, 1341, '2007-10-21 17:17:43', 'Reaper', 482, 47, '2007-10-17 11:15:19', 'So Dardel, what exactly does it do? I would install it and see, but I don\\''t want to accidentaly screw anything up on my other mods.', 'yes', '', 31);
INSERT INTO `forum_posts` VALUES(483, 1312, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 're:Reaper', 482, 47, '2007-10-17 13:37:09', 'Ok thanks for looking at it first of all, and I can assure you that it will not interfere with any other thing that you have installed.\r\n\r\nReaper is a mod that I have been working on for a while. It does a lot of different things, but alot of the things it does is still only accessible from the chat line so it''s hard to see unless you type in the commands.\r\n\r\nI''ll put up a few of the features that it does now. Later, I will give you more descriptive information about it.\r\n\r\nHere''s a short list of what it does, and where applicable I have listed the command associated with it.\r\n\r\nI won''t bother going over the things you can check in the box because it is pretty self explanatory.\r\n\r\nThere are certain key words you can type to someone that has the mod running and it will whisper the person back with information. You can turn on all, none or some of these types of features.\r\n\r\nFor instance, if you type /w Dardel items\r\nit will list to you the contents of my bags that I have enabled and show you in [Link] form what I have.\r\n\r\nHere''s some more things you can type, I am going to use my name in the examples, but replace that with whoever is running the mod.\r\n\r\n/w Dardel stats\r\n This will give you information about Dardel such as Strength, Agility, Intelligence... etc.\r\n\r\n/w Dardel eq\r\n This will show you what items I have equipped in [Link] form.\r\n\r\n/w Dardel craft [search pattern]\r\n/w Dardel craft st\r\n/w Dardel [craft subtype] [search pattern]\r\n These commands will allow you to view the person''s craftable items in [Link] form, and will also list mats when I am done.\r\n \r\n/w Dardel keys\r\n Will show you what keys I have. It will when I am done show you attunements also.\r\n/w Dardel guild\r\n Eventually this will allow other people to see some basic guild information.\r\n/w Dardel pxp (on or off)\r\n  This will turn on or off the Party XP messages. If you have this turned on, it will show your xp gains to other party members.\r\n/w Dardel follow\r\n This will make Dardel follow you if he has the option enabled.\r\n\r\nThose are some of the whisper commands that other people can do even if they don''t have the mod.\r\n\r\nIf you are running the mod the following commands can be used to either do a function or enable or disable features.\r\n\r\n/rp show.............displays interface\r\n/rp hide.............hides interface\r\n/rp minishow.........displays minimap button\r\n/rp minihide.........hides minimap button\r\n/rp on...............turn all replies on\r\n/rp off..............turn all replies off\r\n/rp eq on............turn on equipment replies\r\n/rp eq off...........turn off equipment replies\r\n/rp items <on|off>...turn on/off items replies\r\n/rp bank <on|off>....turn character into the guild bank\r\n/rp bag <#> <on|off>.turn on/off bag # replies\r\n/rp stats <on|off>...turn on/off stats replies\r\n/rp craft <on|off>...turn on/off craft replies\r\n/rp keys <on|off>....turn on/off keys replies\r\n/rp guild <on|off>...turn on/off guild info replies\r\n/rp rs...............restack items in backpacks - will take two or more stacks of items and try to combine them\r\n/rp si <#>...........links items in bag # to guild chat prefixed with Who wants?:\r\n/rp st <#>...........links items in bag # to trade channel prefixed with WTS \r\n/rp aslist...........lists items that are on your Auto Sell list\r\n/rp asremove #.......removes an item from the auto sell list\r\n/rp asadd <item>.....adds an item (by name) to the auto sell list\r\n/rp asthresh <#>.....sets threshold for auto sell (USE WITH CAUTION!!!)    \r\n  0=Poor 1=Normal 2=Uncommon 3=Rare 4=Epic 5=Legendary\r\n/rp aselist..........lists items to be excluded from auto sell\r\n/rp aseremove #......removes an item from the auto sell exclude list\r\n/rp aseadd <item>....adds an item (by name) to the auto sell exclude list\r\n/rp asethresh #......sets threshold for auto sell exclusions\r\n  0=Poor 1=Normal 2=Uncommon 3=Rare 4=Epic 5=Legendary\r\n/rp bank.................Turns on "Bank Mode" where you can list items throughout your inventory to people who inquire\r\n/g items [search pattern] - list items from guild members to your chat\r\n\r\n\r\nSo alot of it is in there and there is some other stuff that I left out but you can''t see it if you don''t know to its there. I recently started adding the actual GUI boxes to it and decided to put it up if anyone wants to help me test it out.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'no', '', 0);
