INSERT INTO `users` VALUES('Terik/Kirak', '12', 'a', '', '', '', 'robinjapan99@hotmail.com', 'yes', '', 'images/no_avatar.gif', '', 0, 1335, '', '', '2007-08-17 18:31:14', 'yes', 'no', 'yes', 0, 1, '2007-10-24 14:07:22', '2007-10-23 08:12:07', '0000-00-00 01:01:01', 255, 4, 18, 'basic|kara|commend', 'ono', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'yes', 'yes', '', 'yes', '32 year single guy who soon to be a full time college student.\r\n\r\nMy rogue is a dagger based backstab tri-build. And my lock is currently a heavy demon spec with some affliction (although I will switch to destruction/demonology once I am 70). Experience wise I''ve played many classes. To include a 63 warrior, 61 priest, 55 hunter, 70 rogue, 67 warlock, 41 druid, 27 shammy, and a 47 mage.\r\n\r\nExperience:\r\nI''ve done a few raids and am fairly familiar with the old school encounters (MC, BWL, AQ, ZG, and Naxx). But I am lacking experience in the newer instances as rogues are not really not popular.\r\n\r\nPrevious Guilds:\r\nI am former member of Guardians of Destiny, Unleashed, and Kingdom of Vengeance.\r\n\r\nWhat I expect:\r\nA good time and to share some laughs. I like to raid and dungeon crawl even if it means spending 5 hours a night doing nothing but wipes to learn an encounter. So you won''t see much complaining from me about wipe or raids that end up bad. Now the big expectation of mine. No drama, there is no need to argue over a game. I can understand a disagreement; but swearing, insults, or back-stabbing is something I won''t tolerate. If there is a problem, take it up with an officer. Of course if I''m the cause of an incident, I expect a reasonable discussion (between myself and the individual, and/or an officer to mediate so as to prevent a situation from affecting the other players/members enjoyment of the game. I don''t mind profanity or jokes, but I don''t abide racism or subjects that others may find offensive. If there is a problem with something I say; I expect anyone to mention it to me so I can rectify the problem instantly. One last thing, I can''t play with people who grief, kill steal, or conduct themselves in a manner that is less than civilized (i.e. arguements in trade/general channels, ninja looting, greed for loot, etc)\r\n\r\nWhat you can expect of me:\r\nWell now that I''m leaving the millitary, I can begin to attend functions and raids without too much trouble. I take raid discipline and ettiquete very seriously (i.e. show up on time, bring all the items you need to complete your tasks, etc). I do not mind running an encounter multiple times in effort to learn it even if I rack up several large repair bills. I always bring items for raids that are in short demand (i.e. jumper cables, repair bots, candles, etc). I don''t mind helping alts crawl through an instance or completing quests. I am becoming more involved with my enchanting, tailoring, and alchemy tradeskills; with that in mind I do not mind making or farming items that will help the guild/members progress. Once I am settled back into my home I will be making keys and faction a priority so I can attend/support guild function.\r\n\r\nMisc Info:\r\nI''m used to playing in rather hardcore guilds so somethings that are more casual or less disciplined are a little odd for me. So please bear with me as I try to adjust to an easier/more fun/less work mentallity.\r\n\r\nAt any rate, if ya need help; just ask. I''m rarely too busy that I can''t spend some time helping out.\r\nI appreciate the invite and should anyone wish to talk about this application, feel free to email me or catch me in game.', 0, '', 'no', 1, 65);
